- 'jewels of the crown' refers to the best-selling items;
- 'shining with both high sales and customer satisfaction' refers to items with high total sales and good average ratings;
- 'grand marketplace of fashion' refers to the clothing items across different categories;
- 'categories that have generated more than $100 in revenue' refers to the condition where the total sales for a category exceed $100.

- "shone the brightest" refers to items with the highest average ratings from the top 5 most recent reviews;
- "popularity in sales" refers to the total quantity of each item sold;
- "availability in stock" refers to the current inventory level of each item.

- "shining stars" refers to the top brands by average rating;
- "total number of reviews" refers to the count of reviews for each brand;
- "revenue they have accumulated" refers to the total revenue generated by each brand.

- 'Casual' and 'Formal' are types of clothing categories;
- 'Average price' is the mean cost of items in a category;
- 'Number of items' refers to the count of clothing items in each category.

- "sold more than 10 items" refers to the number of orders placed for items associated with each brand;
- "total revenue" is calculated by summing the total cost of all orders for each brand;
- "number of items sold" is the count of unique order IDs for each brand.

- "Top 10" implies the highest values in a list, sorted in descending order;
- "Revenue" is the total financial income generated from sales;
- "Clothing items" are specific products in the inventory, each identified by a unique `item_id`;
- "Categories" and "styles" are classifications of clothing items, represented by `category_name` and `style_name` respectively.

- "Total revenue" refers to the total amount of money generated by the item sales;
- "Total returns" refers to the number of items returned by customers;
- "Average rating" is the average customer satisfaction score given to the item.

- "Loyal customers" refer to those who have placed at least two orders;
- "Woven a tapestry of at least two purchases" metaphorically means having made two or more orders;
- "Rating that shines brighter than a three-star average" means an average rating greater than 3.

- Sales rank is based on the total quantity sold;
- Revenue rank is based on the total revenue generated (quantity sold * price);
- Profit rank is based on the total profit (total revenue - cost);
- The NTILE function divides the items into four equal groups (quartiles) for each ranking category.

sql:
SELECT 
  (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN price > 50 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) / COUNT(item_id)) * 100 AS percentage_of_expensive_products
FROM clothing_items;

